Name: fallopian tube endometriosis
Definition: A female reproductive system disease characterized by the growth of endometrial tissue that is located_in the fallopian tube.

Name: endosalpingiosis
Definition: A female reproductive system disease characterized by the growth of fallopian tube-like epithelium outside the fallopian tube.

Name: endometriosis of rectovaginal septum and vagina
Definition: A female reproductive system disease characterized by the growth of endometrial tissue that is located_in the rectovaginal septum and vagina.

Name: endometriosis of ovary
Definition: A female reproductive system disease characterized by the growth of endometrial tissue that is located_in the ovary.
